data.name: Pickled Cucumbers with Dill
data.quickTastyDescription: A refreshing, tangy side dish that's perfect for adding a crunch to any meal!
detailedCookingInstructions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly and slice them into spears or rounds, as preferred.
In a mixing bowl, combine water, white vinegar, salt, and granulated sugar. Stir until dissolved.
Add fresh dill, sliced garlic, and black peppercorns to the mixture.
Place the cucumber slices in a jar and pour the pickling liquid over them until fully submerged.
Seal the jar and refrigerate for at least 24 hours for best flavor.
data.detailedName: Quick Pickled Cucumbers with Fresh Dill
data.modifiersForBase: Add fresh herbs and spices for extra flavor.
